  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: the primary experimental dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-14T00:00:00Z, which predates the modelRevisionDate of 2025-11-03T00:00:00Z by approximately three weeks. The assessment narrative argues this revision was a mesh-topology refinement that did not alter boundary conditions or fluid properties and therefore did not invalidate the experimental reference data; however, no formal re-validation study was conducted against the revised model build.",
