      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (4.2 M, 8.7 M, 17.1 M cells) were generated with refinement ratio r = 1.44. GCI for the relative hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point is 3.8%, satisfying the acceptance criterion. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Mesh study performed on the revised model geometry (post-2025-11-03 build)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "In-vitro test conditions (fluid properties, rotational speed, flow rates) match CFD boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Experimental runs used bovine blood analog (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s ± 0.1 mPa·s) at 37 °C. Flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min; rotational speed to ±15 rpm. CFD boundary conditions replicate these values. Temperature drift < 0.3 °C during test runs. Conditions documented in the experimental protocol archived with dataset fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-2025q4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted RH index within ±15% of experimental measurement at each of the 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Comparison of CFD to experimental RH values across all 5 operating points yields a maximum absolute relative error of 11.3% (at 6 L/min / 2500 rpm) and a root-mean-square error of 7.6%. All points fall within the ±15% acceptance band. Uncertainty in experimental hemolysis measurement (±8% at 95% confidence) has been propagated and does not alter the pass/fail determination."
    },
