      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the FDA-recognised metric for comparative hemolysis assessment of blood-contacting devices. It directly quantifies erythrocyte damage relative to a predicate device, linking CFD output to clinical and regulatory outcomes. The QoI selection is justified in the modelling report and endorsed by the clinical advisory panel."
    },
    {
